==English==

===Etymology===
(1640-50) From French [[faible]] ("[[feeble]]").

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪbəl|-ɔɪbəl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A [[quirk]], [[idiosyncracy]], or [[mannerism]]; unusual [[habit]] or [[way]] (usage is typically plural)
#: ''Try to look past his '''foibles''' and see the friendly fellow underneath.''
# A weakness or failing of character.
# {{fencing}} Part of a sword between the middle and the point, weaker than the [[forte]].

====Synonyms====
*[[fault]]

